The paper focuses on machine learning models trained on data distributed across multiple edge nodes, which suggests a primary category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses resource constraints, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of control algorithms and optimization techniques could also place the paper in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
